<p>Ok, stop! Check this out, it's <em>really</em> cool. What <em>is</em> an application? Well, it's
a set of bundles, a collection of services, and a list of routes. And would you
look at that! We have exactly three methods that define the <em>three</em> things that make
up a framework.</p>
<h2 id="single-file-symfony">Single-File Symfony <a class="headerlink" href="micro-kernel#single-file-symfony" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Let's make a real-live app in just this one file. First, register some bundles:</p>
