<p>Oh, and yea, you <em>can</em> still load YML and XML config files, and you probably will.
I'll mention that soon.</p>
<p>At this point, this app will <em>already</em> work. But let's make a page. In <code>configureRoutes()</code>,
we receive a shiny new <code>RouteCollectionBuilder</code> object - <em>another</em> new thing for
Symfony 2.8 that makes adding routes in PHP a lot more fun than it used to be.</p>
<p>Add a route with <code>$routes-&gt;add('/hello/symfony/{version}')</code>. The second argument
is the controller: pass it <code>kernel:helloSymfony</code>:</p>
