<p>This is the <em>service</em> format for configuring a controller: <code>kernel</code> is the name
of the service - that actually points to <em>this</em> object - and <code>helloSymfony</code> is
the name of the method.</p>
<p>Hey, let's build that:  <code>public function helloSymfony()</code>. Give it a <code>$version</code> argument
and say <code>return new Response('Hi Symfony version '.$version);</code>:</p>
