</p>
<p>This is one of the best and worst parts of the <code>MicroKernel</code>. If you're accustomed
to having twenty bundles, then you're accustomed to having <em>all</em> the features of
Symfony. But, with the <code>MicroKernel</code> you must opt into each feature. The <code>is_granted()</code>
comes from Symfony's <code>SecurityBundle</code>... and we're not using that! If we need it, then
you'll need to add it to <code>LittleKernel</code> and configure your <code>security.yml</code> file.</p>
<p>For now, remove <code>is_granted()</code>:</p>
