        <tbody class="js-tr-container">
                <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-expandable" data-range="1-38" data-last="0">
                <i class="fa fa-arrows-v js-icon-load-more" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show Lines" data-placement="left"></i>
                <i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin js-icon-loading"></i>
            </td>
            <td class="gap-line">
                                                    ... lines 1 - 38
                            </td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-displayed" data-line-number-displayed="39"></td>
            <td class="blob-code">    <span class="hljs-keyword">protected</span> <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">configureContainer</span><span class="hljs-params">(ContainerBuilder $c, LoaderInterface $loader)</span></td>
            </tr>
    <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-expandable" data-range="40-48" data-last="1">
                <i class="fa fa-arrows-v js-icon-load-more" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show Lines" data-placement="left"></i>
                <i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin js-icon-loading"></i>
            </td>
            <td class="gap-line">
                                                    ... lines 40 - 48
                            </td>
            </tr>

        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>
</p>
<p>See that <code>$loader</code> variable? It has an <code>import()</code> method on it - use that to import a
<code>config.yml</code> file and you're done. This is the PHP-equivalent to the <code>imports</code> line in YAML.</p>
<p>Go play with it: I hope you love it as much as I do!</p>

    
